<% content_for :title, "FAQ – Dark Factory" %>

<div class="faq-page">
  <nav class="faq-nav">
    <%= link_to "← Back to board", root_path %>
  </nav>

  <h1 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

  <div class="faq-list">
    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2 class="faq-question">What is Dark Factory?</h2>
      <p class="faq-answer">
        Dark Factory is an AI-powered feature request management system. You submit a feature
        request describing what you want built, and an AI agent autonomously implements it —
        writing the code, opening a pull request, and tracking the work through a Kanban board
        from <em>Todo</em> all the way to <em>Done</em>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2 class="faq-question">How do I submit a feature request?</h2>
      <p class="faq-answer">
        From the <a href="<%= root_path %>">home page</a>, fill in the <strong>Title</strong>
        and <strong>Body</strong> fields and hit <em>Submit</em>. Be as specific as possible —
        the clearer your description, the better the AI agent can understand and implement your
        request. Once submitted, your card will appear in the <em>Todo</em> column and the agent
        will pick it up automatically.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2 class="faq-question">How does the AI agent work?</h2>
      <p class="faq-answer">
        When a feature request is picked up, an AI agent reads your description, plans the
        implementation, and writes the necessary code changes. You can watch its progress in
        real time on the feature request detail page — every tool call, file edit, and decision
        is streamed as an event log. When the agent finishes, it opens a pull request and moves
        the card to <em>To Review</em>. If something goes wrong, the card moves to
        <em>Failed</em> with a reason so you can refine and resubmit.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2 class="faq-question">Does Dark Factory support tree-structured feature requests?</h2>
      <p class="faq-answer">
        Yes! You can break a large feature into a tree of smaller, related requests. Submit a
        parent request describing the high-level goal, then submit child requests for each
        sub-task. The Kanban board keeps all related cards linked so you can track progress
        across the entire tree — from root to leaf — in one place.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h2 class="faq-question">What is your refund policy?</h2>
      <p class="faq-answer">
        If you are not satisfied with Dark Factory, we offer refunds within 30 days of purchase.
        To request a refund, visit our <%= link_to "refund page", refund_path %> and fill out
        the form. Refunds are typically processed within 5–7 business days. If you have any
        questions about your refund, please reach out to our support team.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-refund">
    <p class="faq-refund__text">Need a refund? We've got you covered.</p>
    <%= link_to "Request a Refund", refund_path, class: "faq-refund__btn" %>
  </div>
</div>
